{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A file placed inside a subdirectory of the watched root is processed, not only files placed directly in the root directory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is real recursive filesystem watching behavior (OS watcher + daemon wiring). MOCK-MISS: this is not just parser logic; it appears when watcher events from nested paths are handed to the pipeline. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: mocked watcher events can hide real non-recursive watcher configuration or platform watcher limits. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by behavior text focused only on filesystem watching and processing; no AI/LLM decisions or multi-agent steps are involved.","test_description":"Start the daemon against a real temporary directory tree, create a nested subdirectory under the watched root, write a file in that subdirectory, and assert one transformed output is produced for that nested file path without restarting the daemon.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The deduplication logic correctly discards a second processing request for the same file path within a configurable time window.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is local dedup state/time-window logic keyed by file path. MOCK-MISS: behavior can be exercised at a single object/function boundary (path + clock inputs) without requiring module handoff. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network/subprocess is required for this specific behavior text. REJECTION-GATE: Integration/System were considered, but behavior text says 'deduplication logic' and does not require real watcher events; a deterministic clock and direct method calls can expose real failures in the dedup rule itself. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified (no AI output dependence).","test_description":"Instantiate dedup component with a configurab